summary:
We had an art party at White Cross Children's Home with Kuya Jefre the Artist who will be making a permanent installation using the art work the kids created during our party. The question is: "What is a star?" and the kids answered by cutting shapes from colored paper. Kuya Jefre put the shapes together on a wall and that will soon be a gobo design which will be projected onto the halls of White Cross. 

SOMETHING NEW TO LEARN TODAY:
Did you know that they are slowly removing the word "orphanage" from our vocab because of it's negative connotations. 

Don't be embarrassed if you didn't know. White Cross is really a children's home.I always saw the name but I never knew not to call it an orphanage. I just learned this last month.

One child proudly boasts "malaki ang bahay ko...yung White Cross." Now, they can add...at may mall kami because the new Rockwell Santolan Town Plaza stands on their property! =) How cool is that?

description:
We had an art party at White Cross Children's Home with Kuya Jefre the Artist who will be making a permanent installation using the art work the kids created during our party. The question is: "What is a star?" and the kids answered by cutting shapes from colored paper. Kuya Jefre put the shapes together on a wall and that will soon be a gobo design which will be projected onto the halls of White Cross. 

SOMETHING NEW TO LEARN TODAY:
Did you know that they are slowly removing the word "orphanage" from our vocab because of it's negative connotations. 

Don't be embarrassed if you didn't know. White Cross is really a children's home.I always saw the name but I never knew not to call it an orphanage. I just learned this last month.

One child proudly boasts "malaki ang bahay ko...yung White Cross." Now, they can add...at may mall kami because the new Rockwell Santolan Town Plaza stands on their property! =) How cool is that?
title: White Cross Children's Home Art Party

summary:
Merry Christmas! Thank you so much to all the wonderful ates and kuyas for your time and your gifts to grant the wishes of the kids of Child Haus. Thank you to the hardworking people of Exakt who have helped to make the wishlist online.

Much love to Lorenzo Manalang, Che Manalang, Nicolo Hallare, Izza Lambino-Hallare, Vince Homer So, Ninang Rose Martinez who help mount this party every year!

Thank you to the companies who have supported our yearly Christmas party through the years.

Thank you Timezone Philippines for the fun free play that the kids and all the volunteers enjoy!

Thank you Victory Liner, Inc. for always transporting the kids and their families. They always look so happy in the bus after a full day of family fun!

Thank you so much to Toys "R" Us Philippines for the very many toys and princess dresses that the kids were so happy to receive. Imagine receiving their Christmas wishes plus gifts from Toys R US! It was the best! 

Thank you to the photographers of PAT DY PHOTOGRAPHY. Thank you once again Francis Perez Photography Francis Perez Biboy Martinez Soriano

Thank you to iflix and COLOR Manila RUN for the give aways and donations

Thank you to BlueWater Day Spa for sponsoring the location for this year's party.

Thank you Ate Maria Izadora Calzado for making sure the kids and the volunteers are fed with healthy yummy food!

Thank you Kuya Tim Yap for taking time out of your busy schedule to always volunteer! Thanks for the snacks we all ate in 5 mins during the Timezone free play portion of the party!

Thank you Breville Phils for providing one of our patients with a slow juicer.She was so happy that you granted her wish!

Thank you to Bench for granting the teen's wishes for fashionable clothes =) 

Thank you to our shoppers Earnie Magboo and Trina Velilla-Milanfor buying the kids wishes.

Thank you to the San Juan Doctors, Dr. Gary Eufemio, Ryan Bang Jefre Manuel Shinifer Widjaja Ricky M. Cańete Arnold Naval Ice Ramirez Villaflores Jhong Dela Cruz Maxine San Agustin Elliza Dawn Aurelio Gaki,K Jewels  and everyone who help make the ChildHaus kids happy!

summary:
Been traveling so much these past few days 🛫Manila🛫Vancouver🛫Toronto🛫Montreal🛫New York🛫 and now we're in Chicago 🇵🇭🇨🇦🇺🇸 

I was thinking of this song I wrote a while back when a woman named Shoanda from Bangladesh working at a store in the NY airport said I looked pretty in my hat & shades. She said she was a radio singer back home but she just moved to NY 8 months ago. I love random convos with strangers 🌎 "Half a million strangers...2 souls from lonely strange worlds a boy and a girl 👫 Half a million strangers...I love a moonlit answer. Epic or disaster? Take your pick 🌝

summary:
EXCLUSIVE: Karylle reveals the best gift she’s received because of ‘It’s Showtime’
3/16/2017 9:09 AM
by: Rhea Manila Santos

With almost seven years of being a host on the Kapamilya noontime show It’s Showtime, Karylle admitted she also gets affected whenever one of her co-hosts gets involved in an issue or any kind of intrigue. “Well I guess I’m very sensitive as a person so definitely. I just want the good things for everyone. So whenever there are bad things napagdadaanan naman pag matatag ka and pag may mga kasama ka at karamay ka which is all of us,” she shared during the Watsons Make Your Summer campaign launch held last March 9 at SM Mall of Asia in Pasay city.

Karylle shared why she especially enjoys her growing friendship with co-host Vice Ganda (which their fans have lovingly dubbed as the “Vicerylle”). The 35-year-old actress said they enjoy laughing a lot on and off cam. “Yeah nung isang araw pinagkakalat niya na, basta may pinagkakalat siya so inamoy ko yung anit niya (laughs). Hindi wala. It’s just a very silly show din. I mean, the world is too serious already. It’s nice to have a light, happy moment everyday,” she admitted.

During the Watson’s summer launch, Karylle dropped by to talk about her love for Belo sun products. She also shared the biggest gift she has received as part of the popular Kapamilya variety show. “I think everyone hopes for a show to always last very long naman. Yes of course the show has changed me in a way. It has brought me closer to a lot of people. People feel more comfortable around me. When you see somebody automatically grabe na yung bond ninyo because they watch it everyday. So that is something parang magical for me kasi traveling around the Philippines or even around the world, it’s a big surprise to know that they’re really invested in the show. So maganda yung connection mo with everyone. So it’s nice to know ang daming buhay ang nababago or napapasaya ng programa,” she explained.

summary:
Karylle teams up with the Child Haus kids and changes roles from big sister to co-singer in this inspiring musical project called Akay.

Akay is a project that advocates Child Haus’ vision mission of allowing those undergoing medical evaluation and treatment to live a happy, healthy and productive life. The song was written by Yael and Karylle Yuzon, and features performances of Child Haus kids Catherine Buenaobra, Earhonel Cayetano, Katrina Cagampang, Jhon Jhoven Lagaras, Mary Joy Patillan, Joseph Ramirez, Mark Lester Tayo & Gideon Yason.

The project also aims to increase awareness on the basic needs of the organization in order to provide the best service possible such as medicine, diapers, food, and other household materials. With the help of MyPledge, becoming a donor is easier than ever.

For more info go to: http://www.anakarylle.com/causes.html

'Akay'
Artists: Karylle feat. Child Haus kids

Catherine Buenaobra, Earhonel Cayetano, Katrina Cagampang, Jhon Jhoven Lagaras, Mary Joy Patillan, Joseph Ramirez, Mark Lester Tayo & Gideon Yason,

Guitar: Edwin Dimaranan
Producer: Alvin Cornista
Composers: Ysmael & Ana Karylle Yuzon
Voice Coach: Lindie Achacoso
Director & Editor: Nani Naguit
Footage from Recording Session by: Julian Rodriguez

data.description: via IG/anakarylle: Super dooper fan mode #gameofthrones #GOTexhibit pila!!!!!!!! Ganto kasi yun...I was jogging around Tuileries and I wandered off to the louvre while waiting for @yaelyraz who's training for his first marathon on Saturday and I chanced upon GOT posters. I wanted to line up but Yael wanted to go back to the apartment to freshen up. On our way back, we took so many detours and ate a late lunch. When we returned, we had just missed the end of the line. I was sooooooo sad. I even lost my new camera shortly after that. 1 guy said I could try again this morning, another 1 said the tickets for today were all out. When I got here, 1 lady said we couldn't go in anymore. But I hung around the entrance and saw a group go in and I didn't see any tickets. Plus there was a new boss guy who was there and OMG he said I just have to wait in line but we can go in!!!! So, I'm waiting in line. I almost cried. I was sooooo happy. Hahahaha #merci #paris

attachments.description:
Karylle shows versatility in K
 
Karylle lights up TV screens everyday via the noontime show Showtime, enchants nightly as Cinderella onstage the Resorts World Newport Performing Arts Theater, and bannered the Filipino Pride flag when she top billed the Pan-Asian musical series The Kitchen Musical. Primarily a singer, Karylle exhibits her versatility in her latest album K, produced by PolyEast Records. It was launched last November 16, at the Glorietta 5 Atrium.

“Every album is a blessing because you get to share parts of yourself to more people,” says Karylle. “I hope people will enjoy the fruits of our labor.”

K features the singer-actress-TV-host dabbling into different genres. She shows her fun side in the catchy pop tune and carrier single Kiss You, goes edgy in the modern upbeat tune Bad Boys (which also has a remix version by DJ MOD), turns sentimental in the ballad "Kapiling Ka", and pays tribute to her musical roots in "In My Own Little Corner" (from Rodgers and Hammerstein’s Cinderella), among others. The album also includes Karylle’s 2013 Philpop entry "Sa’yo Na Lang Ako."
